1
00:00:48,949 --> 00:00:51,483
<i>OH, MAN.</i>
<i>WHAT DID HE SAY?</i>

2
00:00:51,551 --> 00:00:55,120
A NATURAL HEAT VORTEX.
THAT'S WHAT HE CALLED IT.

3
00:00:55,188 --> 00:00:57,122
AND HE WAS RIGHT.

4
00:00:57,190 --> 00:00:59,390
SEE OUT THERE?

5
00:00:59,459 --> 00:01:03,929
THE COOL BREEZES
FROM THE OCEAN MIXING WITH
THE STEAMIN' DESERT AIR...

6
00:01:03,998 --> 00:01:05,931
MAKE, LIKE, A BIG...

7
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:10,101
WIND COLLISION THING,
AND THAT'S WHAT RUNS
THE WINDMILLS.

8
00:01:10,170 --> 00:01:12,904
YOU FIGURED THAT OUT
BY YOURSELF?

9
00:01:12,973 --> 00:01:15,006
NOT ME. JAROD.

10
00:01:15,075 --> 00:01:18,410
<i> [ Bird Screeches ]</i>
DID IT BY WATCHING THEM.

11
00:01:18,479 --> 00:01:22,146
<i>WITHOUT MOVING A MUSCLE,</i>
<i>THEY CAN JUST...</i>

12
00:01:22,215 --> 00:01:23,949
HOVER IN THE VORTEX.

13
00:01:24,018 --> 00:01:26,752
HE JUST SAT IN THIS SPOT
ALL DAY.

14
00:01:26,821 --> 00:01:30,622
JUST EATIN' PEZ
AND TAKING IN THE HAWKS.

15
00:01:30,691 --> 00:01:35,260
I'M SURPRISED YOUR DR. DOLITTLE
DIDN'T TRY TALKING TO THEM.

16
00:01:35,329 --> 00:01:38,129
<i>WELL, IT WASN'T JUST</i>
<i>THE BIRDS HE WAS INTO.</i>

17
00:01:38,198 --> 00:01:40,865
HE REALLY DUG THESE.

18
00:01:40,934 --> 00:01:46,137
HE'D, LIKE, BE THROWING
DUST AT 'EM ALL DAY,
SAYING HE WAS FIGURING THE...

19
00:01:46,206 --> 00:01:49,107
UPDRAFTS AND
THE AIR CURRENTS AND STUFF.

20
00:01:49,176 --> 00:01:51,743
- RIGHTEOUS, HUH?
- LOVELY.

21
00:01:54,848 --> 00:01:57,649
OH, JAROD.

22
00:01:57,718 --> 00:02:00,251
WHAT ARE YOU UP TO NOW?

23
00:02:03,624 --> 00:02:06,858
<i> WHOO-HOO!</i>

24
00:02:06,927 --> 00:02:08,794
<i>[ Laughing ]</i>

25
00:02:10,363 --> 00:02:12,297
THAT WAS GREAT!

26
00:02:15,068 --> 00:02:17,735
CONGRATULATIONS.
YOU JUST BEAT THE GAUNTLET.

27
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:19,738
THIS IS SO COOL.

28
00:02:21,542 --> 00:02:25,844
WELL, JAROD,
THE AUDITION'S OVER.
YOU WANT THE JOB, IT'S YOURS.

29
00:02:25,913 --> 00:02:27,845
WANT IT? I COULD
STAY UP HERE FOREVER.

30
00:02:28,415 --> 00:02:30,415
<i> HEE-HEE!</i>

31
00:02:32,552 --> 00:02:36,054
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>

32
00:03:26,740 --> 00:03:30,608
WELL, MR. MATTHEWS,
FOR AN EX-FIGHTER JOCK, YOU'VE
DONE PRETTY GOOD FOR YOURSELF.

33
00:03:30,677 --> 00:03:35,247
WELL, YEAGER SELLS BATTERIES.
I'VE GOT SKYVIONICS.
A BUCK'S A BUCK.

34
00:03:35,316 --> 00:03:38,583
THE END OF THE COLD WAR NEARLY
KILLED MOST OF THE DEFENSE
CONTRACTORS,

35
00:03:38,652 --> 00:03:42,086
YET YOUR STOCK'S UP, WHAT,
17% LAST QUARTER ALONE?

36
00:03:42,155 --> 00:03:44,889
EIGHTEEN.
WHOO! MAYBE I SHOULD
BUY ME A LITTLE.

37
00:03:44,958 --> 00:03:47,892
WELL, WITH THE SCIMITAR
CHIP ABOUT TO BE APPROVED,

38
00:03:47,962 --> 00:03:51,729
MAYBE YOU SHOULD
BUY YOURSELF A LOT.

39
00:03:51,798 --> 00:03:56,001
IS THAT A DRAKEN?
YEAH. UNCLE SAM'S NOT THE ONLY
ONE WITH A SHRINKING PURSE.

40
00:03:56,070 --> 00:03:59,371
WE'RE TESTING THE SCIMITAR
IN PLANES FROM THE R.A.F.,
THE ISRAELIS.

41
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:01,573
HELL, EVEN THE FROGS
SENT OVER A MIRAGE.

42
00:04:01,641 --> 00:04:03,942
YOU SEEN DIXON?
YEAH. THERE'S
THE WILD MAN NOW.

43
00:04:05,679 --> 00:04:09,681
<i> HE'S A GOOD PILOT,</i>
<i> BUT PUNCTUALITY'S</i>
<i> NOT HIS THING.</i>

44
00:04:09,749 --> 00:04:11,616
<i> HE'LL PROBABLY MISS</i>
<i> HIS OWN FUNERAL.</i>

45
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:23,262
- YOU'RE LATE.
- YEAH, BUT WHAT AN ENTRANCE.

46
00:04:23,330 --> 00:04:27,199
- SO, HOW'D HE DO?
- ONLY TOOK HIM ONE WEEK TO DO
THREE WEEKS' WORTH OF TESTS.

47
00:04:27,267 --> 00:04:29,934
- THAT MAKES HIM THE NEW
KING OF THE MOUNTAIN.
- YOU SERIOUS?

48
00:04:30,003 --> 00:04:31,970
HE SCORED 34%.

49
00:04:32,039 --> 00:04:35,707
- AH, IT WAS NO BIG DEAL.
-<i> OH, IT IS WHEN DIX HERE</i>
<i> ONLY SCORES 33.</i>

50
00:04:35,776 --> 00:04:37,976
EVEN SO, I WANT YOU TO
SHADOW THIS HOTSHOT.

51
00:04:38,045 --> 00:04:40,545
HE'LL SHOW YOU EVERYTHING
YOU NEED TO KNOW
ABOUT THE NEW SYSTEM.

52
00:04:40,613 --> 00:04:43,715
<i> THEN YOU CAN TEACH HIM</i>
<i> HOW TO BEAT THE GAUNTLET.</i>
<i> AT THE END OF THE WEEK,</i>

53
00:04:43,784 --> 00:04:47,485
I'LL DECIDE WHO GETS TO BE MY
WINGMAN FOR THE PENTAGON TEST.

54
00:04:47,554 --> 00:04:49,655
NO PRESSURE.

55
00:04:53,227 --> 00:04:56,094
SO, JAROD, I HEARD YOU RAN SOME
FLIGHTS FOR THE AGENCY.

56
00:04:56,162 --> 00:04:59,364
WHO WAS YOUR POINT MAN?
ANDREW STERLING.

57
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:01,600
ORIGINAL SECRET AGENT MAN.

58
00:05:01,668 --> 00:05:05,303
YEAH, I RAN SOME TR-1 RECONS
OVER SINGAPORE FOR HIM
BACK IN THE '80s.

59
00:05:05,372 --> 00:05:07,872
NORTH KOREA.

60
00:05:07,941 --> 00:05:10,041
RIGHT.

61
00:05:10,110 --> 00:05:13,878
WELL, I CAN'T BELIEVE
I'M ACTUALLY FLYING
FOR MANHUNTER MATTHEWS.

62
00:05:13,947 --> 00:05:16,214
HE'S THE SECOND-BEST PILOT
I'VE EVER SEEN.

63
00:05:16,283 --> 00:05:18,283
AND WHO'S THE BEST?

64
00:05:19,819 --> 00:05:21,819
YOU'RE LOOKING AT HIM.

65
00:05:33,233 --> 00:05:37,201
HOW DOES IT FEEL UP THERE?
AH, SMOOTH. I CAN'T WAIT
TO GET THIS BABY BACK UP.

66
00:05:37,270 --> 00:05:40,605
BODY BY F-16.
BRAINS BY YOURS TRULY.

67
00:05:40,673 --> 00:05:45,343
<i>THE SCIMITAR CHIP MAKES ANY</i>
<i>PLANE'S ONBOARD COMPUTER WORK</i>
<i>10 TIMES AS FAST AS THE OTHERS.</i>

68
00:05:45,412 --> 00:05:48,446
WELL, IN THIS GAME,
SPEED MEANS LIFE.

69
00:05:48,514 --> 00:05:52,217
GLAD TO SEE TOM'S FINALLY GOT
HIMSELF SOME A1 JOCKS
TO KEEP UP.

70
00:05:52,286 --> 00:05:54,219
QUALITY CONTROL PROBLEMS?

71
00:05:54,288 --> 00:05:56,321
MR. LAWSON.
DEPENDS ON WHO YOU ASK.

72
00:05:56,390 --> 00:05:58,690
I'D APPRECIATE THE LATEST
HYDRAULIC SPECS.

73
00:05:58,759 --> 00:06:01,993
- YOU'RE BEGINNING TO SOUND LIKE
A BROKEN RECORD, LIEUTENANT.
- QUICK WAY TO FIX THAT.

74
00:06:02,062 --> 00:06:04,796
YES, MA'AM.

75
00:06:08,802 --> 00:06:11,969
<i>[ Lieutenant ]</i>
<i>STEREOGRAPHS. THEY SAY THERE'S</i>
<i>A PICTURE IN THERE SOMEWHERE,</i>

76
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:14,740
<i>BUT I'VE NEVER</i>
<i>BEEN ABLE TO SEE ONE.</i>

77
00:06:14,808 --> 00:06:17,875
A PENGUIN AT THE SPHINX.
A PENGUIN RIDING A CAMEL.

78
00:06:18,979 --> 00:06:20,912
A PENGUIN ON A NILE BARGE.

79
00:06:20,981 --> 00:06:23,281
NOW THAT'S SOMETHING
YOU DON'T SEE VERY OFTEN.

80
00:06:23,350 --> 00:06:25,784
I COULD LOOK AT THESE THINGS
FOR A WEEK. NOTHING.

81
00:06:25,853 --> 00:06:27,819
WELL, IT'S ALL IN
THE OCULAR MUSCLES.

82
00:06:27,888 --> 00:06:29,921
THE KEY IS YOU FOCUS
ON THE POSTER,

83
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:32,557
BUT YOU MOVE YOUR PRIMARY
EYESIGHT EIGHT DEGREES
TO THE LEFT.

84
00:06:32,626 --> 00:06:34,659
<i> [ Lieutenant ]</i>
<i> WHAT DID YOU DO?</i>
<i> INVENT THESE THINGS?</i>

85
00:06:34,728 --> 00:06:36,994
<i> MMM. NOT OFFICIALLY.</i>

86
00:06:37,064 --> 00:06:39,598
JAROD WRIGHT.
YOU'RE RONALD COLLINS'S
REPLACEMENT.

87
00:06:39,666 --> 00:06:42,000
LIEUTENANT JANICE GANT.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

88
00:06:42,068 --> 00:06:44,069
PENGUIN, HUH?

89
00:06:44,137 --> 00:06:46,104
PENGUIN.

90
00:06:55,048 --> 00:06:57,649
I SEE YOU MET
MISS CONGENIALITY.

91
00:06:57,717 --> 00:06:59,717
TOUGHEST S.P.O.
IN THE FIELD.

92
00:06:59,786 --> 00:07:02,820
AH. SO SHE'S
THE SPECIAL PROJECTS OFFICER.

93
00:07:02,889 --> 00:07:05,690
BLUE-SUITERS SENT HER
TO KEEP TABS ON US.

94
00:07:05,758 --> 00:07:09,727
WHICH REMINDS ME.
CLEARVIEW RIDGE.
NATURAL HEAT VORTEX.

95
00:07:09,796 --> 00:07:11,729
WIND SHEAR UP THE WAZOO.

96
00:07:11,798 --> 00:07:14,932
YOU LEAN ON THE THROTTLE
ANYWHERE NEAR THERE,
AND SHE'LL BLOW A GASKET.

97
00:07:15,001 --> 00:07:18,069
CLEARVIEW RIDGE.
THANKS FOR THE TIP.

98
00:07:22,709 --> 00:07:25,643
<i>[ Plane Engine Roaring ]</i>

99
00:08:38,785 --> 00:08:42,854
<i>[ Young Sydney ]</i>
<i>DON'T TELL ME WHAT YOU SEE,</i>
<i>JAROD. TELL ME WHAT YOU FEEL.</i>

100
00:08:47,727 --> 00:08:49,694
TELL ME WHAT YOU FEEL.

101
00:08:49,763 --> 00:08:53,098
I FEEL TIRED.
MY LEGS HURT.

102
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:57,235
<i>[ Young Sydney ]</i>
<i>PUSH WITH THE PAIN. FOCUS.</i>
<i>WE NEED DETAILS.</i>

103
00:08:58,405 --> 00:09:00,337
THIS HELMET'S TOO TIGHT.

104
00:09:02,475 --> 00:09:04,409
IT'S HOT.

105
00:09:04,477 --> 00:09:06,877
I DON'T LIKE THIS.

106
00:09:06,946 --> 00:09:10,248
<i>WHY CAN'T I GET A BIKE</i>
<i>THAT ACTUALLY GOES SOMEWHERE?</i>

107
00:09:10,951 --> 00:09:12,583
SYDNEY.

108
00:09:12,652 --> 00:09:14,919
<i> SYDNEY.</i>

109
00:09:21,161 --> 00:09:23,094
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

110
00:09:46,386 --> 00:09:48,419
<i> [ Knocking On Door ]</i>

111
00:09:48,488 --> 00:09:50,521
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>JUST A MINUTE.</i>

112
00:09:54,694 --> 00:09:59,030
HELLO, MR. HOLLIS.
HOW ARE YOU?
FINE. SUPER. GREAT.

113
00:09:59,099 --> 00:10:02,900
<i>CAN I HELP YOU WITH SOMETHING?</i>
WHY DO YOU NEED
A SECOND PHONE LINE?

114
00:10:02,969 --> 00:10:05,370
IT'S FOR MY MODEM.
I'M UPLOADING SOMETHING.

115
00:10:05,439 --> 00:10:07,571
OH. ONE OF THOSE.

116
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:11,242
- ONE OF THOSE?
- SHEEP. PEOPLE WHO DON'T MIND
GIVING UP THEIR PRIVACY.

117
00:10:11,311 --> 00:10:13,711
- BAA!
- EXCUSE ME?

118
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:15,780
IT'S TOO LATE.
THEY KNOW.

119
00:10:15,848 --> 00:10:19,450
- THEY?
- THE BLACK HELICOPTERS.
THE GRAY MEN.

120
00:10:19,519 --> 00:10:21,485
LIKE THOSE SKYVIONICS PEOPLE.

121
00:10:21,554 --> 00:10:25,557
I'VE BEEN ON THAT PLACE.
BEEN OUT THERE
SINCE WORLD WAR II...

122
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:28,627
DOING SOME VERY
COCKAMAMY THINGS.

123
00:10:30,130 --> 00:10:32,764
WHAT'S IN THE CASE?

124
00:10:32,833 --> 00:10:34,766
- MEMORIES.
- PICTURES?

125
00:10:34,834 --> 00:10:37,769
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

126
00:10:37,837 --> 00:10:41,305
WHY WOULD YOU WANT
A COMPUTER IF I GAVE YOU
A PERFECTLY GOOD TV?

127
00:10:41,374 --> 00:10:45,442
SEE? UNIVERSAL REMOTE EVEN.
RUNS EVERYTHING
BUT YOUR LIFE.

128
00:10:45,511 --> 00:10:49,414
YES. BUT THEY COULD BE
WATCHING YOU THROUGH THE TV.

129
00:10:49,483 --> 00:10:53,584
NO REVERSE-IMAGING DEVICE.
I INSPECTED IT.

130
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:56,354
<i> I ALSO TOOK THE LIBERTY...</i>

131
00:10:56,423 --> 00:11:00,792
OF PROGRAMMING THIS
TO SKIP CHANNELS WITH
SUBLIMINAL MIND CONTROL.

132
00:11:00,860 --> 00:11:03,661
WELL, THAT WAS VERY CONSIDERATE
OF YOU, MR. HOLLIS.

133
00:11:03,730 --> 00:11:07,498
YOU AREN'T UPLOADING
FILTHY PICTURES, ARE YOU?

134
00:11:07,567 --> 00:11:12,303
WELL, THAT DEPENDS
ON HOW YOU DEFINE FILTHY.

135
00:11:19,412 --> 00:11:23,214
<i> [ Broots ]</i>
<i> IT CAME DOWN THE LINE</i>
<i> JUST A FEW MINUTES AGO.</i>

136
00:11:23,283 --> 00:11:25,216
JAROD.

137
00:11:25,285 --> 00:11:27,218
<i>THIS BETTER BE GOOD, SYD.</i>

138
00:11:29,256 --> 00:11:32,690
<i> MR. RAINES?</i>
<i> HOW DID HE FIND OUT</i>
<i> ABOUT HIM?</i>

139
00:11:32,759 --> 00:11:36,127
<i>MUST BE THE DISKS FROM</i>
<i>THE DIGITAL SIMULATION ARCHIVE.</i>

140
00:11:36,195 --> 00:11:38,329
DO YOU THINK HE REALIZES
WHAT IT MEANS?

141
00:11:38,398 --> 00:11:40,965
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT JAROD.

142
00:11:41,034 --> 00:11:43,801
IF HE DOESN'T NOW,
HE SOON WILL.

143
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:46,404
<i>HE IS A GENIUS.</i>

144
00:11:46,473 --> 00:11:49,573
YOU CAN STRETCH IT,

145
00:11:49,642 --> 00:11:54,411
BOUNCE IT
AND COPY NEWSPRINT WITH IT,

146
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:56,547
AND IT COMES IN ITS OWN
PLASTIC EGG.

147
00:11:56,616 --> 00:12:01,486
YEAH. SEE, THE EGG IS LIKE
A SYMBOL OF THIS STUFF'S BIRTH,
YOU KNOW?

148
00:12:01,554 --> 00:12:04,856
<i>ITS BEING.</i>
<i> IT'S NOT JUST PUTTY.</i>

149
00:12:04,924 --> 00:12:07,524
IT'S WHATEVER
YOU WANT IT TO BE.

150
00:12:08,761 --> 00:12:11,429
OH.

151
00:12:11,498 --> 00:12:14,499
WELL, WHY WOULD THEY CALL
SOMETHING THIS VERSATILE SILLY?

152
00:12:14,568 --> 00:12:16,734
WOULD YOU BUY SOMETHING
CALLED VERSATILE PUTTY?

153
00:12:16,803 --> 00:12:20,104
I DON'T KNOW.
BUT I'LL BUY THIS.

154
00:12:20,173 --> 00:12:22,373
I'LL BUY 100.

155
00:12:23,609 --> 00:12:25,676
COOL.

156
00:12:48,901 --> 00:12:50,901
[ Bicycle Bell Rings ]

157
00:13:58,538 --> 00:14:00,471
HELLO. YOU MUST BE JAROD.

158
00:14:00,540 --> 00:14:02,473
[ Mouthing Words ]

159
00:14:05,111 --> 00:14:07,644
WE'LL BE VERY HAPPY
TO HELP YOU WITH THAT.

160
00:14:12,752 --> 00:14:14,818
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>THE VIEW IS BETTER</i>
<i>FROM THE INSIDE.</i>

161
00:14:18,491 --> 00:14:22,393
THOUGHT I SMELLED SOME SMOKE.
EVERYTHING SEEMS TO BE A-OKAY.

162
00:14:22,461 --> 00:14:24,295
GOOD.

163
00:14:24,363 --> 00:14:26,830
NEVER FIGURED YOU
FOR A PILOT.

164
00:14:26,899 --> 00:14:29,634
WELL, IF IT MAKES YOU
FEEL ANY BETTER,
I'M NOT REALLY A PILOT.

165
00:14:29,703 --> 00:14:31,302
OH, RIGHT.
I'M JIMMY HOFFA.

166
00:14:31,371 --> 00:14:34,305
COULD HAVE TOLD ME.

167
00:14:34,373 --> 00:14:38,543
MAN LIKES TO KNOW WHEN
HE'S ABOUT TO HAVE HIS THROAT
RIPPED OUT AND FED TO HIM.

168
00:14:38,611 --> 00:14:40,811
IT DIDN'T SEEM IMPORTANT.

169
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:43,014
IMPORTANT?

170
00:14:43,083 --> 00:14:45,083
DOES THAT LOOK IMPORTANT?

171
00:14:45,151 --> 00:14:48,686
FLEETS OF THESE BEHEMOTHS,
LIKE CRAZED FLYING MONKEYS,

172
00:14:48,755 --> 00:14:51,589
TERRORIZING U.S. CITIZENS
FROM SEATTLE TO MIAMI.

173
00:14:51,658 --> 00:14:53,658
TERRORIZING?

174
00:14:54,760 --> 00:14:59,230
HALCION GAS.
C.I.A. CREATED IT IN 1971.

175
00:14:59,299 --> 00:15:03,000
1969.
I KNEW IT.
YOU'RE ONE OF THEM.

176
00:15:03,069 --> 00:15:05,335
WOULD YOU STOP, PLEASE?

177
00:15:07,073 --> 00:15:10,541
THIS IS A MASS HALLUCINOGEN.
THIS IS PRETTY POTENT.

178
00:15:13,613 --> 00:15:17,715
HELL, YOUR DENTIST
HAS STRONGER STUFF.

179
00:15:17,783 --> 00:15:20,283
EVEN SO, I CAUGHT
AN ACCIDENTAL WHIFF.

180
00:15:20,352 --> 00:15:23,420
THOUGHT I WAS
ELEANOR ROOSEVELT FOR
THE BEST PART OF AN AFTERNOON.

181
00:15:23,489 --> 00:15:27,558
YOUR POINT BEING?
REMEMBER THE MEDFLY?

182
00:15:27,627 --> 00:15:30,060
NO SUCH THING.

183
00:15:30,129 --> 00:15:32,696
LOCK YOUR DOORS
AND BOLT YOUR WINDOWS,
AMIGO.

184
00:15:32,765 --> 00:15:35,766
THE EXTERMINATOR'S COMING,
AND HIS NAME IS SKYVIONICS.

185
00:15:35,834 --> 00:15:39,470
SKYVIONICS?
MERCHANTS OF DEATH.
TRUST ME.

186
00:15:39,538 --> 00:15:41,939
I'VE BEEN A CLOWN
IN THAT CIRCUS,

187
00:15:42,007 --> 00:15:44,908
AND IT'S ANYTHING
BUT THE GREATEST SHOW
ON EARTH.

188
00:16:05,197 --> 00:16:07,198
<i> [ Chattering ]</i>

189
00:16:07,266 --> 00:16:09,266
<i> ♪♪ [ Country ]</i>

190
00:16:10,436 --> 00:16:14,505
<i>♪♪ [ Singing In Spanish ]</i>

191
00:16:14,574 --> 00:16:17,040
THAT'S QUITE A COLLECTION.

192
00:16:17,109 --> 00:16:21,745
THE ONLY THING WE HAVE NOW
TO HANG UP THERE IS YOU,
THE SKYVIONIC BOYS,

193
00:16:21,814 --> 00:16:23,780
SINCE WE DON'T HAVE
A BASE ANYMORE.

194
00:16:23,849 --> 00:16:25,782
WHAT'S YOUR POISON?

195
00:16:25,851 --> 00:16:28,618
- EXCUSE ME?
- WHAT'S YOUR DRINK?

196
00:16:28,687 --> 00:16:32,089
UH, I WAS RAISED ON OPTIMIZED
NUTRITIONAL SUPPLEMENTS:

197
00:16:32,158 --> 00:16:35,426
HEARTS OF PALM,
WHEATGRASS, ASPARAGUS
MIXED WITH TOMATO.

198
00:16:35,495 --> 00:16:37,928
VIRGIN MARY,
CELERY GARNISHED.

199
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:41,365
UH, COULD YOU MAKE IT
TWO, PLEASE?
I'M EXPECTING COMPANY.

200
00:16:41,433 --> 00:16:43,000
MM-HMM.

201
00:17:00,719 --> 00:17:04,388
WHAT THE HELL DO YOU THINK
YOU WERE DOING UP THERE?

202
00:17:04,457 --> 00:17:07,558
PRACTICE MAKES PERFECT.
YOU KNOW WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT, WRIGHT.

203
00:17:07,626 --> 00:17:09,560
CLEARVIEW RIDGE.

204
00:17:09,629 --> 00:17:11,962
I WAS RETRACING
RONALD COLLINS'S LAST FLIGHT.

205
00:17:13,299 --> 00:17:16,333
<i>TWO VIRGIN MARYS.</i>

206
00:17:16,402 --> 00:17:18,769
I HOPE THIS IS YOUR POISON.

207
00:17:25,744 --> 00:17:29,012
- YOU KNEW I'D COME AFTER YOU.
- TOUGHEST S.P.O. IN THE FIELD.

208
00:17:29,081 --> 00:17:31,014
AT LEAST THAT'S WHAT
THEY TELL ME.

209
00:17:34,086 --> 00:17:36,019
<i> SO, LIEUTENANT GANT,</i>

210
00:17:36,088 --> 00:17:39,389
WHY IS THE AIR FORCE
SO CONCERNED WITH
A CIVILIAN FLIER?

211
00:17:39,458 --> 00:17:43,327
YOU'RE TESTING A SYSTEM
THAT'S DESIGNED TO PROTECT
MILITARY PILOTS.

212
00:17:43,395 --> 00:17:45,362
IT'S MY JOB TO MAKE SURE
IT'S SAFE.

213
00:17:45,431 --> 00:17:47,364
AND I'M UP FOR WINGMAN
ON FRIDAY'S TEST.

214
00:17:47,433 --> 00:17:49,967
I DON'T FLY AVIONICS
I'M NOT FAMILIAR WITH.

215
00:17:50,036 --> 00:17:52,235
IT'S MY JOB TO KNOW
WHAT I'M GETTING INTO.

216
00:17:52,304 --> 00:17:54,204
TRUE.

217
00:17:54,273 --> 00:17:58,409
NOW, FROM WHAT I UNDERSTAND,
COLLINS HAD PLENTY OF TIME
TO EJECT.

218
00:17:58,477 --> 00:18:01,011
TIME, YES.

219
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:03,514
ABILITY, NO.

220
00:18:03,582 --> 00:18:05,449
HIS RECORD IN THE GULF
SAYS OTHERWISE.

221
00:18:05,517 --> 00:18:08,084
WELL, BETWEEN ME AND YOU
AND THAT WALL OF FAME,

222
00:18:08,153 --> 00:18:10,754
COLLINS DIDN'T EJECT
BECAUSE HE BLACKED OUT.

223
00:18:10,823 --> 00:18:13,223
<i> WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?</i>

224
00:18:13,291 --> 00:18:16,793
PUT IT THIS WAY.
HIS DRINK OF CHOICE
WAS NOT A VIRGIN MARY.

225
00:18:16,862 --> 00:18:19,897
IS THAT TRUE?
YOU CAN TAKE MY WORD FOR IT,

226
00:18:19,966 --> 00:18:23,600
OR STEAL MY REPORT FROM
THE SPECIAL PROJECTS OFFICE
IN D.C.

227
00:18:23,669 --> 00:18:25,903
NOW THAT WOULD BE IMPOSSIBLE.

228
00:18:27,706 --> 00:18:33,043
LOOK, NOT EVEN HIS WIFE
FOUGHT THE ALLEGATIONS,
AND THEY COST HER HIS PENSION.

229
00:18:33,112 --> 00:18:37,381
TWO SKYVIONICS EMPLOYEES
PLACE COLLINS RIGHT HERE
IN THIS VERY BAR...

230
00:18:37,450 --> 00:18:39,416
<i>THE NIGHT BEFORE THE CRASH.</i>
WHO?

231
00:18:41,653 --> 00:18:43,586
<i>LAWSON, FOR ONE.</i>

232
00:18:43,655 --> 00:18:45,222
WHO ELSE?

233
00:18:45,291 --> 00:18:47,157
TOM MATTHEWS.

234
00:18:50,896 --> 00:18:53,931
<i>[ Matthews On Radio ]</i>
<i>NICE FLYING, JAROD.</i>
<i>BRING IT ON HOME.</i>

235
00:18:58,470 --> 00:19:02,606
YOU WEREN'T KIDDING WHEN YOU
SAID YOU WERE A QUICK STUDY.
AH. BEGINNER'S LUCK.

236
00:19:02,675 --> 00:19:05,375
WE'RE MAKING A BIG ANNOUNCEMENT
AFTER THE TEST.

237
00:19:05,444 --> 00:19:07,410
SCIMITAR'S GOING COMMERCIAL.

238
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:11,849
BY THE YEAR 2000,
THAT SCIMITAR CHIP'S GONNA BE ON
EVERY AIRLINER IN THE COUNTRY.

239
00:19:11,917 --> 00:19:13,917
I FEEL SAFER ALREADY.

240
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:17,788
WELL, I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW
I'VE BEEN TALKING TO CORPORATE
TYPES ABOUT YOU.

241
00:19:17,857 --> 00:19:20,390
YOU'RE OUR BEST FLIER,
HANDS DOWN.

242
00:19:20,459 --> 00:19:24,795
BUT?
BUT I GOTTA GIVE THE TEST
TO DIXON ON FRIDAY.

243
00:19:24,864 --> 00:19:28,098
I UNDERSTAND.
YOU DON'T WANT A REPEAT
OF THE LAST TEST.

244
00:19:28,167 --> 00:19:32,269
WE WON'T.
THIS TIME NO TEST PILOT'S
GONNA LET ME DOWN.

245
00:19:32,337 --> 00:19:34,804
RON COLLINS COULD HAVE
FLOWN CIRCLES AROUND YOU TWO.

246
00:19:34,873 --> 00:19:38,275
INSTEAD HE HIT THE BOTTLE.
I'M SURPRISED YOU MISSED THAT.

247
00:19:38,344 --> 00:19:41,545
I CALLED HIM ON IT
THE MORNING OF THE TEST.
HE SAID HE WAS FINE.

248
00:19:41,614 --> 00:19:43,380
SO IT WASN'T
A MECHANICAL FAILURE.

249
00:19:43,449 --> 00:19:45,849
THE RESIDUAL ALCOHOL
IN HIS BLOOD...

250
00:19:45,918 --> 00:19:48,852
CAUSED HIM TO BLACK OUT
WHEN HE PULLED TOO MANY G'S.

251
00:19:48,921 --> 00:19:50,887
COLLINS WAS FLYING A SAFE PLANE.

252
00:19:50,956 --> 00:19:53,123
I'M SURE HE WAS.

253
00:20:19,752 --> 00:20:22,185
IS YOUR MOM HOME?

254
00:20:22,254 --> 00:20:24,654
MOM!

255
00:20:24,723 --> 00:20:26,723
YOU WERE WITH RON
IN SAUDI ARABIA?

256
00:20:26,792 --> 00:20:30,360
YOUR HUSBAND-- HE SAVED
MY TAIL ON THE THIRD NIGHT
OVER BAGHDAD.

257
00:20:30,429 --> 00:20:33,397
<i> WHEN I HEARD ABOUT</i>
<i> THE ACCIDENT, I--</i>

258
00:20:33,465 --> 00:20:37,601
<i> WELL, I TRIED TO</i>
<i> MAKE MY WAY HERE</i>
<i> AS SOON AS I COULD.</i>

259
00:20:37,670 --> 00:20:39,736
I WANT TO TELL YOU
HOW SORRY I AM.

260
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:46,209
ME AND A COUPLE OF
THE GUYS, WE PETITIONED
THE C.N.O.'s OFFICE...

261
00:20:46,278 --> 00:20:49,078
ABOUT GETTING RON
A POSTHUMOUS
GULF WAR COMMENDATION.

262
00:20:50,316 --> 00:20:52,949
WHAT'S WRONG, MOM?

263
00:20:54,386 --> 00:20:56,320
NOTHIN'.

264
00:20:56,388 --> 00:20:59,189
THAT'S GREAT.
THAT'S REALLY GREAT.

265
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:03,626
HAVE YOU HAD SUPPER YET?

266
00:21:08,167 --> 00:21:10,200
YOU'RE SAYING JAROD
LEFT THIS FOR US.

267
00:21:10,268 --> 00:21:12,936
WHEN I TRIED TO SAVE
THIS PICTURE OF MR. RAINES,

268
00:21:13,005 --> 00:21:16,974
IT UNZIPPED AN EXECUTABLE
THAT CREATED THIS PROGRAM.

269
00:21:17,042 --> 00:21:20,710
AND I'LL BE ABLE TO COMMUNICATE
WITH HIM AND SEE HIM?

270
00:21:20,779 --> 00:21:22,913
THROUGH HIS ENCRYPTION,
YES.

271
00:21:25,584 --> 00:21:28,218
I DON'T WANT MISS PARKER
TO FIND OUT ABOUT THIS.

272
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:31,054
UH, WAIT-- WAIT A MINUTE.

273
00:21:31,123 --> 00:21:34,724
UH, YOU WANT TO PLAY
POLITICAL PARCHEESI
WITH THE ICE QUEEN, YOU GO--

274
00:21:34,793 --> 00:21:36,326
[ Growls ]

275
00:21:36,394 --> 00:21:41,164
YOU GO RIGHT AHEAD,
BUT I'M NOT DANCING
IN THAT MINEFIELD. NO WAY.

276
00:21:41,233 --> 00:21:45,902
[ Laughing ]
YOU ARE AFRAID
OF LOSING YOUR JOB.

277
00:21:47,639 --> 00:21:49,939
I'M AFRAID OF LOSING MY LIFE.

278
00:21:54,880 --> 00:21:58,982
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>HEY. YOU GET HOT DOGS AND</i>
<i>MACARONI FOR DINNER EVERY NIGHT?</i>

279
00:22:00,019 --> 00:22:02,319
I WISH.

280
00:22:03,922 --> 00:22:06,490
IT'S QUITE A VIEW, HUH?

281
00:22:06,558 --> 00:22:08,492
THAT'S ORION, THE HUNTER.

282
00:22:08,560 --> 00:22:11,261
AND THAT ONE'S PEGASUS.
THE WINGED HORSE.

283
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:17,234
THAT WAS DAD'S FAVORITE.
I CAN NAME A LOT OF STARS.
DAD AND I STUDIED 'EM.

284
00:22:17,303 --> 00:22:20,804
WE WENT TO SEE 'EM IN THE DESERT
THE NIGHT BEFORE HE LEFT.

285
00:22:22,875 --> 00:22:24,807
REALLY?

286
00:22:24,877 --> 00:22:27,344
- JUST YOU AND YOUR DAD?
- SHH.

287
00:22:27,412 --> 00:22:29,812
MOM NEVER LIKED IT
WHEN WE SNUCK OUT LATE.

288
00:22:29,882 --> 00:22:32,482
WE NEVER TOLD HER.

289
00:23:02,113 --> 00:23:04,180
<i> HEY, JAROD.</i>
<i> DON'T FORGET.</i>

290
00:23:04,249 --> 00:23:06,816
TOMORROW I NEED YOU TO
PLAY BOGEY IN THE DRAKEN.

291
00:23:06,885 --> 00:23:09,819
- WHERE IS IT?
- THEY'RE PREPPING IN NUMBER 27.

292
00:23:09,888 --> 00:23:12,322
- THAT'S TWO HANGARS DOWN.
- THANKS.

293
00:23:12,391 --> 00:23:14,391
HOW MANY HOURS YOU LOGGED
IN ONE OF THOSE?

294
00:23:14,459 --> 00:23:16,726
WELL, ACTUALLY,
THIS'LL BE MY...

295
00:23:16,795 --> 00:23:18,995
FIRST.

296
00:23:23,568 --> 00:23:25,702
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>LOOKS LIKE JAROD'S BEEN BUSY.</i>

297
00:23:25,771 --> 00:23:29,839
<i>THIS IMAGE WAS TAKEN LAST NIGHT</i>
<i>BY ONE OF OUR KH-11 SATELLITES.</i>

298
00:23:29,908 --> 00:23:32,776
THAT'S LA GRANGE.
MM-HMM.

299
00:23:32,844 --> 00:23:37,013
LA GRANGE?
ONE OF THE CENTRE'S PRIVATE,
UNMARKED AIRSTRIPS.

300
00:23:37,082 --> 00:23:40,050
THAT'S SOMEWHERE
IN VIRGINIA, RIGHT?
<i>RIGHT. IT'S JUST OUTSIDE OF D.C.</i>

301
00:23:40,119 --> 00:23:44,754
THIS SHOT'S
JUST BEFORE 2:00 A.M.
NOTHING UP THE SLEEVE, RIGHT?

302
00:23:44,823 --> 00:23:46,690
<i>AND PRESTO.</i>

303
00:23:46,758 --> 00:23:50,026
[ Mispronouncing ]
DRAKEN JET.
DRAKEN.

304
00:23:50,095 --> 00:23:53,963
OH. PARKED THERE
FOR THREE HOURS UNTIL--

305
00:23:54,032 --> 00:23:58,635
- POOF.
- HE LANDED THERE IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE NIGHT, UNDETECTED?

306
00:23:58,703 --> 00:24:02,739
AND THREE HOURS
GIVES HIM PERFECT TIME
FOR A VISIT TO D.C.

307
00:24:02,807 --> 00:24:04,741
WHY WASHINGTON?

308
00:24:30,502 --> 00:24:32,468
[ Gant ]
LIEUTENANT JANICE GANT
REPORTING.

309
00:24:32,537 --> 00:24:34,470
S.P.O. VIDEO RECORD.

310
00:24:34,539 --> 00:24:37,407
COLLINS/MATTHEWS
DOGFIGHT SIMULATION.

311
00:24:37,476 --> 00:24:41,078
[ Matthews On Radio ]
SCIMITAR 2, COME IN.
DO YOU COPY, HAMMER?

312
00:24:41,146 --> 00:24:44,181
[ Collins ]
UH, ROGER THAT, MANHUNTER.
SYSTEM IS HOT AND WORKING GREAT.

313
00:24:44,249 --> 00:24:46,216
[ Matthews ]
LET'S TRY THAT AGAIN
AT MACH 1.8.

314
00:24:46,285 --> 00:24:49,386
- THROW IN A SHOULDER ROLL
FOR GOOD MEASURE.
- COME AND GET ME, MANHUNTER.

315
00:24:51,323 --> 00:24:54,624
<i>[ Matthews ]</i>
<i>COMING IN FOR THE KILL.</i>
<i>SAY YOUR PRAYERS, HAMMER.</i>

316
00:25:01,566 --> 00:25:04,334
<i>[ Matthews ]</i>
<i>PULL OUT OF THE ROLL, COLLINS.</i>
<i>PULL OUT OF THE ROLL.</i>

317
00:25:04,403 --> 00:25:06,569
<i>YOU'RE HEADIN' DOWN.</i>
<i>LEVEL OFF.</i>

318
00:25:06,638 --> 00:25:08,571
<i>LEVEL OFF, COLLINS!</i>

319
00:25:08,640 --> 00:25:10,573
<i>COLLINS, PUNCH OUT!</i>

320
00:25:10,642 --> 00:25:12,575
<i>LEVEL OFF, COLLINS.</i>
<i>YOU'RE GOING DOWN.</i>

321
00:25:12,644 --> 00:25:16,045
<i>GET OUT OF THERE.</i>
<i>PUNCH OUT! PUNCH OUT!</i>

322
00:25:16,114 --> 00:25:18,882
<i>COLLINS! COLLINS!</i>

323
00:25:20,118 --> 00:25:22,852
YOU COULDN'T PUNCH OUT...

324
00:25:22,921 --> 00:25:26,423
BECAUSE MATTHEWS SENT YOU UP
IN AN UNSAFE PLANE.

325
00:25:34,199 --> 00:25:37,266
IF YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND,
WE'LL JUST TRY AGAIN. OKAY?

326
00:25:37,335 --> 00:25:39,202
[ Mouths Words ]

327
00:25:43,541 --> 00:25:45,942
[ Mouthing Words ]

328
00:25:54,619 --> 00:25:56,553
VERY GOOD.

329
00:26:12,337 --> 00:26:15,638
- LISTEN TO ME, DOCTOR.
- [ No Audible Dialogue ]

330
00:26:20,345 --> 00:26:22,278
<i>LISTEN TO ME, DOCTOR.</i>

331
00:26:22,347 --> 00:26:24,480
THE KID ASKS ABOUT
HIS FATHER AGAIN,

332
00:26:24,549 --> 00:26:27,884
<i>TELL HIM DADDY</i>
<i>LOVED HIM VERY MUCH,</i>

333
00:26:27,953 --> 00:26:30,287
<i>AND DADDY DIED</i>
<i>IN A PLANE CRASH.</i>

334
00:26:30,355 --> 00:26:32,521
THAT'S NOT EXACTLY A LIE.

335
00:26:32,590 --> 00:26:34,658
<i>ARE WE CLEAR?</i>

336
00:26:38,830 --> 00:26:41,230
"ARE WE CLEAR?"

337
00:26:42,367 --> 00:26:45,001
<i>[ Glass Shatters ]</i>
<i>[ Man Yelling ]</i>

338
00:26:45,069 --> 00:26:50,440
<i>[ Hollis Shouting ]</i>

339
00:26:59,851 --> 00:27:02,052
MR. HOLLIS?
<i>[ Hollis ]</i>
<i>GET ME OUT OF HERE.</i>

340
00:27:02,120 --> 00:27:04,754
MR. HOLLIS.
<i>[ Shouting ]</i>

341
00:27:06,258 --> 00:27:08,191
MR. HOLLIS.
[ Shouting ]

342
00:27:08,259 --> 00:27:11,361
<i> IT'S OKAY. IT'S JAROD.</i>
<i> IT'S JAROD.</i>

343
00:27:12,530 --> 00:27:14,898
JAROD.

344
00:27:14,966 --> 00:27:17,934
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

345
00:27:18,002 --> 00:27:20,136
NIGHTMARE.
[ Sighs ]

346
00:27:20,204 --> 00:27:23,540
SHOULDN'T YOU BE
UPLOADING SOMETHING?

347
00:27:39,224 --> 00:27:42,024
HIROSHIMA.

348
00:27:42,093 --> 00:27:43,827
THIS IS YOU.

349
00:27:43,896 --> 00:27:46,696
GREATEST SHOW ON EARTH.

350
00:27:46,765 --> 00:27:50,099
<i>I WAS PART OF SOMETHING THAT...</i>

351
00:27:50,168 --> 00:27:52,569
SHOULD HAVE NEVER HAPPENED.

352
00:27:55,974 --> 00:27:58,407
I HELPED DO THIS.

353
00:28:10,655 --> 00:28:13,356
YOU COULDN'T HAVE KNOWN.

354
00:28:13,424 --> 00:28:17,928
<i>IGNORANCE IS A POOR EXCUSE...</i>

355
00:28:17,996 --> 00:28:20,596
FOR MURDER.

356
00:29:02,574 --> 00:29:05,341
<i>[ TV Channels Switching ]</i>

357
00:29:40,679 --> 00:29:44,013
<i> [ TV Channels Switching ]</i>

358
00:29:44,082 --> 00:29:47,850
[ Quietly Imitating Gunfire ]

359
00:29:50,421 --> 00:29:54,190
-<i> [ Woman On TV ] STOP THIS CAR.</i>
<i>  STOP IT OR I'LL--</i>
- [ Imitating Continues ]

360
00:29:55,693 --> 00:29:59,495
140 CHANNELS, NOTHING ON.

361
00:30:01,032 --> 00:30:04,367
YEAH. MY WIFE SAYS
I'LL DIE WITH ONE OF
THOSE THINGS IN MY HAND.

362
00:30:04,436 --> 00:30:06,436
HMM.

363
00:30:08,306 --> 00:30:11,341
BROKE?
DEFECTIVE.

364
00:30:12,344 --> 00:30:14,611
HEY, YOU'RE
THE MECHANICAL WHIZ.

365
00:30:14,680 --> 00:30:17,814
THE SPECS SAY THERE'S
A FAILURE RATE OF 0.4%.

366
00:30:17,882 --> 00:30:19,849
SO?

367
00:30:19,918 --> 00:30:23,253
SO, I'VE DONE MY OWN
CALCULATIONS, AND I'VE COME UP
WITH A FAILURE RATE OF...

368
00:30:23,321 --> 00:30:25,822
3.1%.

369
00:30:31,496 --> 00:30:33,430
SOUNDS LIKE A BAD CHIP.

370
00:30:35,033 --> 00:30:37,033
YOU'RE THE EXPERT.

371
00:30:42,540 --> 00:30:45,441
THAT'S A SCIMITAR CHIP.
MM-HMM.

372
00:30:45,510 --> 00:30:49,679
AND WHEN IT FAILS,
WHOLE PLANE'S AFFECTED.

373
00:30:51,082 --> 00:30:54,017
ALTITUDE CONTROLS,

374
00:30:54,085 --> 00:30:56,719
INFRARED SIGHTING,

375
00:30:56,788 --> 00:30:59,489
EJECTION SYSTEMS.

376
00:30:59,558 --> 00:31:03,359
RONALD COLLINS DIDN'T PUNCH OUT
THE NIGHT OF THE CRASH
BECAUSE HE COULDN'T.

377
00:31:04,595 --> 00:31:07,230
3.1%.

378
00:31:07,299 --> 00:31:11,200
IS THAT WHAT A MAN'S LIFE
IS WORTH AT SKYVIONICS?

379
00:31:11,269 --> 00:31:14,537
HE WASN'T AT THE TAIL FIN BAR
DRINKING THE NIGHT BEFORE
THE CRASH.

380
00:31:14,606 --> 00:31:16,672
HE WAS OUT IN THE DESERT.

381
00:31:16,741 --> 00:31:19,109
HE WAS STARGAZING
WITH HIS SON.

382
00:31:20,212 --> 00:31:22,145
WHY DID YOU LIE?

383
00:31:27,785 --> 00:31:30,753
I, UH--
I WARNED MATTHEWS
ABOUT THE CHIP,

384
00:31:30,822 --> 00:31:34,324
BUT HE SAID THE RATIO
WAS ACCEPTABLE.

385
00:31:34,392 --> 00:31:38,228
"3.1 IS NOTHING
AGAINST THE BOTTOM LINE."

386
00:31:39,831 --> 00:31:43,600
IS THAT WHY YOU DOCTORED
THE VOICE RECORDER?

387
00:31:43,669 --> 00:31:45,634
YEAH.

388
00:31:45,703 --> 00:31:48,071
MATTHEWS WANTED TO KEEP
GANT OUT OF THE LOOP.

389
00:31:48,139 --> 00:31:52,008
HE SAID WE'D ALL BE
RAKING IT IN ONCE HE CLOSED
THE COMMERCIAL CONTRACTS.

390
00:31:52,077 --> 00:31:54,077
[ Scoffs ]

391
00:31:57,482 --> 00:31:59,482
<i>JAROD.</i>

392
00:32:00,985 --> 00:32:04,053
<i>PUT YOURSELF IN MY SHOES.</i>

393
00:32:04,122 --> 00:32:06,389
I ALREADY HAVE.

394
00:32:08,059 --> 00:32:10,060
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

395
00:32:17,235 --> 00:32:19,535
WHO IS THAT MAN?

396
00:32:19,604 --> 00:32:22,772
IT'S NO ONE, JAROD.
IT'S NO ONE.

397
00:32:22,840 --> 00:32:25,709
<i>[ Beeps ]</i>
ANSWER THE QUESTION, SYDNEY.

398
00:32:27,813 --> 00:32:31,580
WHO IS HE?
AND WHAT DOES HE KNOW
ABOUT MY FATHER?

399
00:32:31,649 --> 00:32:33,616
SYDNEY, I'M NOT HERE.

400
00:32:35,586 --> 00:32:39,122
I'M GLAD WE CAN
FINALLY TALK AGAIN.

401
00:32:42,493 --> 00:32:44,894
THE PLANE CRASH
IS "NOT EXACTLY A LIE."

402
00:32:44,963 --> 00:32:46,896
WHAT DID HE MEAN BY THAT?

403
00:32:46,965 --> 00:32:50,533
I ONLY KNOW HIM AS MR. RAINES.

404
00:32:50,602 --> 00:32:53,669
BUT LISTEN, JAROD.
I'VE BEEN SEARCHING HERE,

405
00:32:53,738 --> 00:32:56,038
<i>AND I'VE DISCOVERED ONE THING.</i>

406
00:32:56,107 --> 00:32:58,708
YOUR FATHER WAS AN AVIATOR.

407
00:32:58,777 --> 00:33:01,343
AN AVIATOR WHO HAD FLOWN WITH--

408
00:33:01,412 --> 00:33:03,746
- JAROD? JAROD!
- SYDNEY?

409
00:33:03,815 --> 00:33:07,016
SYDNEY? SYDNEY!

410
00:33:08,953 --> 00:33:10,653
SYDNEY.

411
00:33:10,722 --> 00:33:12,755
DAMN.

412
00:33:12,823 --> 00:33:15,057
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>WELL, SOMEBODY INSIDE</i>
<i>CUT US OFF.</i>

413
00:33:15,126 --> 00:33:17,093
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>THAT'S RIGHT.</i>

414
00:33:17,161 --> 00:33:19,228
COME WITH ME.

415
00:33:42,253 --> 00:33:44,887
LIEUTENANT GANT,
IT'S JAROD WRIGHT.

416
00:33:44,956 --> 00:33:46,956
THERE'S SOMETHING
THAT YOU REALLY SHOULD SEE.

417
00:33:51,329 --> 00:33:53,396
UNIFORMS-R-US?

418
00:33:53,465 --> 00:33:55,431
I NEED A RUSH JOB.

419
00:34:33,371 --> 00:34:36,605
I THOUGHT WE HAD
AN UNDERSTANDING.

420
00:34:36,674 --> 00:34:40,176
AND NOW... THIS.

421
00:34:41,512 --> 00:34:44,380
WELL, HE TALKED ME INTO IT.

422
00:34:44,448 --> 00:34:46,548
HE FORCED ME.

423
00:34:46,617 --> 00:34:48,618
HE'S NOT THAT GOOD.

424
00:34:50,488 --> 00:34:52,988
I CAN MAKE IT UP TO YOU.

425
00:34:59,697 --> 00:35:01,730
AND HOW DO YOU PROPOSE
TO DO THAT?

426
00:35:03,768 --> 00:35:07,670
JAROD'S TRANSMISSION USED
AN OLD ARPA CONNECTION
FROM THE EARLY INTERNET DAYS...

427
00:35:07,738 --> 00:35:10,039
WHEN IT WAS STILL
A DEFENSE DEPARTMENT SYSTEM.

428
00:35:10,108 --> 00:35:13,375
I'VE ZEROED IN
ON HIS LOCATION.

429
00:35:26,191 --> 00:35:29,192
IT'S A BEGINNING.
[ Coughs ]

430
00:35:31,396 --> 00:35:34,830
LIEUTENANT.
SIR. WE SHOULD BE STARTING
IN ABOUT 30 MINUTES, SIR.

431
00:35:34,900 --> 00:35:39,235
GOOD. BEEN WAITING SIX YEARS
FOR THIS SCIMITAR SYSTEM
TO IMPRESS US.

432
00:35:39,304 --> 00:35:42,238
BETTER BE NOW.
TRUST ME, SIR.
AFTER WHAT I SAW LAST NIGHT,

433
00:35:42,307 --> 00:35:44,240
IT'S GONNA BE
A REAL EYE-OPENER.

434
00:35:44,308 --> 00:35:46,909
<i>[ Matthews ]</i>
<i>WHAT DO YOU MEAN</i>
<i>YOU CAN'T FIND DIXON?</i>

435
00:35:46,978 --> 00:35:50,947
I'M SORRY, SIR.
THERE'S NO ANSWER AT HIS HOME.
HE'S PROBABLY ON HIS WAY.

436
00:35:51,015 --> 00:35:54,484
ALL RIGHT. YOU TELL CONTROL
TO CONFIRM THAT ALL SYSTEMS
ARE ON LINE.

437
00:35:54,552 --> 00:35:57,086
<i>YES, SIR.</i>
AND CALL
DIXON'S HOUSE AGAIN.

438
00:35:57,155 --> 00:35:59,155
[ Hissing ]

439
00:36:08,699 --> 00:36:11,301
<i> [ Phone Ringing ]</i>

440
00:36:21,946 --> 00:36:24,280
<i>[ Ringing Continues ]</i>

441
00:36:26,184 --> 00:36:28,217
[ Line Ringing ]

442
00:36:28,286 --> 00:36:30,286
NOTHING.

443
00:36:37,795 --> 00:36:40,329
[ Jarod ]
THE NATIVES MUST BE
GETTING RESTLESS.

444
00:36:40,398 --> 00:36:42,331
YOU UP FOR A DOGFIGHT?

445
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:46,068
ME? I WAS BORN FOR THIS MOMENT.

446
00:36:47,639 --> 00:36:49,939
[ Matthews On Radio ]
ALL RIGHT.
YOU KNOW THE DRILL.

447
00:36:50,008 --> 00:36:51,941
[ Jarod ]
JUST LIKE WE PRACTICED.

448
00:36:52,010 --> 00:36:55,077
DON'T BREAK MACH 1.
DON'T GET FANCY.

449
00:36:55,146 --> 00:36:58,013
WE'LL BE OPEN-MIKED
INTO THE TOWER,
SO REMEMBER,

450
00:36:58,082 --> 00:37:00,783
WE'RE ON THE AIR,
AND EVERYTHING'S
ON THE LINE.

451
00:37:00,851 --> 00:37:03,586
I WOULDN'T HAVE IT
ANY OTHER WAY.

452
00:37:03,655 --> 00:37:05,587
<i> ALL RIGHT. HERE WE GO.</i>

453
00:37:05,656 --> 00:37:09,892
SCIMITAR 2, WHY DON'T YOU
MAKE LIKE A BANDIT?

454
00:37:09,961 --> 00:37:11,961
ROGER THAT, MANHUNTER.

455
00:37:17,001 --> 00:37:20,069
<i>[ Matthews Over Speaker ]</i>
<i>FIRST STOP, RADAR REFLECTION.</i>

456
00:37:20,138 --> 00:37:23,906
<i>SCIMITAR'S ADVANCED AVIONICS</i>
<i>WILL ENABLE EAGLE'S R.W.R....</i>

457
00:37:23,975 --> 00:37:26,809
<i>TO INITIATE LOCKUP</i>
<i>TWICE AS FAST</i>
<i>AS COMPETITIVE SYSTEMS.</i>

458
00:37:26,878 --> 00:37:30,712
<i>AS HE EVADES,</i>
<i>SCIMITAR WILL PREDICT</i>
<i>HIS ANGLE OFF-TAIL...</i>

459
00:37:30,781 --> 00:37:33,115
<i>AND LOCK ON A REAL MISSILE.</i>

460
00:37:33,184 --> 00:37:36,085
<i>IN THE AIR, SPEED IS LIFE,</i>
<i>AND SCIMITAR IS SPEED.</i>

461
00:37:36,154 --> 00:37:38,921
- [ Beeping ]
- BANG.

462
00:37:38,990 --> 00:37:41,857
<i>YOU'RE DEAD, EAGLE.</i>
I ALWAYS WONDERED
WHAT THAT FELT LIKE.

463
00:37:41,927 --> 00:37:44,460
<i>[ Matthews ]</i>
<i>OKAY.</i>
<i>[ Jarod ] LET'S TRY THIS AGAIN.</i>

464
00:37:44,529 --> 00:37:46,796
<i>MACH 1.8.</i>
<i>LET'S REALLY TEST THE SYSTEM.</i>

465
00:37:46,864 --> 00:37:48,865
ROGER THAT.

466
00:37:49,700 --> 00:37:52,802
<i> [ Beeping ]</i>

467
00:37:52,870 --> 00:37:55,371
<i>[ Matthews ]</i>
<i>JAROD, WE'RE OFF THE SPEAKER.</i>
<i>WHAT DO YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING?</i>

468
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:58,774
-<i> YOU WANT TO LOOK GOOD IN FRONT</i>
<i>  OF THE BRASS, DON'T YA?</i>
- YOU FOLLOW MY LEAD.

469
00:37:58,843 --> 00:38:00,776
I REALLY COULDN'T DO THAT.

470
00:38:00,845 --> 00:38:05,148
YOU SEE, THERE'S A FAILURE RATE
OF 3.1% ON ANY PROMISE I MAKE.

471
00:38:05,216 --> 00:38:07,150
RONALD COLLINS WASN'T SO LUCKY.

472
00:38:08,286 --> 00:38:10,219
<i>COME AND GET ME, MANHUNTER.</i>

473
00:38:13,491 --> 00:38:15,691
ALL RIGHT, GENERAL.
WATCH AND LEARN.

474
00:38:19,230 --> 00:38:21,030
SIR.

475
00:38:21,098 --> 00:38:24,767
- WHAT THE DEVIL
IS THIS ALL ABOUT?
- THE TRUTH, GENERAL.

476
00:38:42,920 --> 00:38:44,920
[ Beeping ]

477
00:38:46,457 --> 00:38:49,858
I'VE LOST FLIGHT CONTROL.

478
00:38:49,927 --> 00:38:51,794
<i>[ Matthews ]</i>
<i>EAGLE, REPEAT:</i>

479
00:38:51,863 --> 00:38:53,796
I'VE LOST FLIGHT CONTROL.

480
00:38:53,865 --> 00:38:56,065
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>THAT'S BECAUSE YOUR SCIMITAR</i>
<i>CHIP HAS FAILED.</i>

481
00:38:56,133 --> 00:38:58,267
<i>JUST LIKE THE ONE</i>
<i>IN RONALD COLLINS'S PLANE.</i>

482
00:38:58,336 --> 00:39:00,236
SCARY, ISN'T IT, TOM?

483
00:39:00,305 --> 00:39:03,038
I CAN'T PUNCH OUT!
I CAN'T PUNCH OUT!

484
00:39:03,108 --> 00:39:06,208
<i> I'LL TELL YOU HOW--</i>
<i> IF YOU TELL ME THE TRUTH.</i>

485
00:39:06,277 --> 00:39:07,944
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

486
00:39:08,012 --> 00:39:10,613
WELL, THEN YOU'RE GONNA SUFFER
THE SAME FATE AS RONALD COLLINS.

487
00:39:10,682 --> 00:39:13,582
<i>DO YOU COPY, MANHUNTER?</i>

488
00:39:13,651 --> 00:39:15,684
I HAD TO MAKE GOOD
ON THE QUARTER!

489
00:39:15,753 --> 00:39:18,621
YOU KILLED A GOOD MAN,
AND THEN YOU BLAMED IT ON HIM.

490
00:39:18,689 --> 00:39:21,390
I DIDN'T WANT THAT TO HAPPEN!
I'M SORRY!

491
00:39:21,459 --> 00:39:24,593
<i>HE WAS A FRIEND OF MINE.</i>
<i>I DIDN'T WANT THAT TO HAPPEN.</i>
<i>GET ME OUT OF HERE!</i>

492
00:39:24,662 --> 00:39:26,795
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>ENABLE YOUR INFRARED SIGHTING.</i>

493
00:39:26,864 --> 00:39:28,530
I.R.'s ON.

494
00:39:28,599 --> 00:39:30,766
DISABLE YOUR
RADAR WARNING RECEIVER.

495
00:39:30,835 --> 00:39:32,602
- CHECK.
-<i> PULL THE EJECT HANDLE.</i>

496
00:39:32,670 --> 00:39:34,703
IT WON'T WORK!
IT STILL WON'T WORK!

497
00:39:35,874 --> 00:39:38,174
<i> OOPS.</i>
<i> I ALMOST FORGOT.</i>

498
00:39:42,513 --> 00:39:43,713
COOL.

499
00:39:49,354 --> 00:39:51,387
<i>LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,</i>
<i>SKYVIONICS RADIO...</i>

500
00:39:51,455 --> 00:39:53,789
HAS REACHED THE END
OF ANOTHER BROADCAST DAY.

501
00:39:53,858 --> 00:39:55,891
THIS IS EAGLE, SIGNING OFF.

502
00:39:57,062 --> 00:39:58,427
LET'S GO.

503
00:39:59,497 --> 00:40:02,798
<i> [ Jarod ]</i>
<i> YEE-HAW!</i>

504
00:40:02,867 --> 00:40:05,400
THIS IS SO COOL.

505
00:40:12,276 --> 00:40:15,177
<i> [ General ]</i>
<i> MATTHEWS.</i>

506
00:40:15,246 --> 00:40:18,647
THE GOVERNMENT WANTS A REFUND.

507
00:41:31,255 --> 00:41:33,689
<i> OH!</i>

508
00:41:33,758 --> 00:41:35,691
YES!

509
00:41:35,760 --> 00:41:37,727
MOM! MOM! COME LOOK AT THIS!

510
00:41:37,795 --> 00:41:40,262
WELL, I GUESS IT'S NOT EASY
LIVING NEXT TO A NUTCASE.

511
00:41:41,933 --> 00:41:44,133
YOU'RE NOT CRAZY,
MR. HOLLIS.

512
00:41:44,202 --> 00:41:46,902
I BELIEVE EVERYTHING
YOU'VE TOLD ME.

513
00:41:46,970 --> 00:41:50,939
<i>I'M STILL NOT SURE ABOUT</i>
<i>THE ELEANOR ROOSEVELT THING.</i>

514
00:41:52,943 --> 00:41:57,113
THERE IS ANOTHER PIECE OF
INFORMATION THAT I'D LIKE YOU
TO KEEP YOUR EYE ON.

515
00:41:57,181 --> 00:41:59,215
WHAT'S THAT?

516
00:42:00,918 --> 00:42:02,851
IT'S IN DELAWARE.

517
00:42:02,920 --> 00:42:04,853
BLUE COVE.

518
00:42:04,922 --> 00:42:06,989
A PLACE CALLED THE CENTRE.

519
00:42:07,058 --> 00:42:10,592
NOW, THAT'S THE ONLY MAP
YOU'RE EVER GONNA
FIND IT ON.

520
00:42:10,661 --> 00:42:15,931
IT'S A DANGEROUS PLACE.
PEOPLE SHOULD BE MADE AWARE,
IF YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

521
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:18,401
OH, YEAH.

522
00:42:18,469 --> 00:42:20,403
THIS IS REAL RIPE.

523
00:42:20,471 --> 00:42:22,471
I'LL SPREAD THE WORD.

524
00:42:22,540 --> 00:42:24,540
I'M COUNTING ON IT.

525
00:42:25,876 --> 00:42:28,144
GOOD LUCK.
YOU TOO.

526
00:42:29,880 --> 00:42:31,813
UH, JAROD.

527
00:42:34,051 --> 00:42:37,953
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT IS YOU'RE AFTER,
BUT I HOPE YOU FIND IT.

528
00:42:55,673 --> 00:42:57,973
<i> ♪♪ [ Country ]</i>

529
00:43:01,345 --> 00:43:03,612
MISS PARKER.

530
00:43:12,957 --> 00:43:15,124
<i> YOU'RE MISS PARKER.</i>

531
00:43:15,193 --> 00:43:17,826
- THAT'S RIGHT.
- HMM.

532
00:43:29,373 --> 00:43:32,241
<i>[ Sam ]</i>
<i>WHAT IS IT?</i>
SILLY PUTTY.

533
00:43:33,244 --> 00:43:35,444
DO YOU HAVE A MIRROR?

534
00:43:41,586 --> 00:43:44,386
"LATE PILOT CLEARED OF ERROR."

535
00:44:05,008 --> 00:44:07,008
NOTHING.

536
00:44:07,077 --> 00:44:12,815
<i>[ Man ] I'M BEGINNING TO DREAD</i>
<i>THAT THE PARKER KILLER INSTINCT</i>
<i>WASN'T HEREDITARY.</i>

537
00:44:12,883 --> 00:44:17,853
- I'LL FIND HIM, SIR.
- LET ME BE PERFECTLY CLEAR.

538
00:44:17,922 --> 00:44:21,456
JAROD IS NOT
SOME MINOR INCONVENIENCE...

539
00:44:21,525 --> 00:44:25,427
FOR YOU TO PAD
YOUR CENTRE EXPENSES WITH.

540
00:44:25,496 --> 00:44:28,030
I UNDERSTAND, MR. RAINES.

541
00:44:52,289 --> 00:44:55,123
WE'RE READY FOR YOU, SIR.

542
00:45:04,802 --> 00:45:06,802
HELP YOURSELF.

543
00:45:10,908 --> 00:45:13,475
<i>[ Applause ]</i>

544
00:45:13,544 --> 00:45:17,712
<i>[ Applause Continues ]</i>
<i>[ Cheering ]</i>

545
00:45:20,984 --> 00:45:22,918
<i>[ Applause Subsides ]</i>

546
00:45:27,291 --> 00:45:30,492
<i>♪♪ [ Classical ]</i>

547
00:46:13,804 --> 00:46:14,903
[ Mews ]

